				<p>If we are located in the northern hemisphere, the ideal building orientation tends to be the south. When talking about orientation, we are referring to the façade that has more openings. A building can have the same façade surface in other directions, but if the majority of the openings are in the southern façade, the orientation considered would be the south.</p>
